Mistakes give us important information. Use your mistakes to guide what you focus on next. What have you learned from your mistakes?

Complete the following questions to practice the skills you have learned in this lesson.

  1. Which of the following is equivalent to \(10^2−12^2\)?

Correct!

Try again. Take a moment to think about what you learned in activity 8.8.2. Are you using it the right way?

The correct answer is \((10 + 12)(10 − 12)\).
